1954;;The Weak and the Wicked;;British;;J. Lee Thompson;;Glynis Johns, Diana Dors;;prison drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Weak_and_the_Wicked;;Frank "women in prison" story that sympathetically tracks several inmates through their imprisonment and subsequent return to society. Some are successfully rehabilitated; some are not.<br><br>Female prisoners talk about the events that brought them there and each of their stories is detailed in a series of flashbacks; the upper-class Jean (Glynis Johns), the brash Betty (Diana Dors) and the pregnant Pat (Rachel Roberts). The film follows the inmates' progress behind bars; Jean's ordeal improves after some sympathetic bonding with her fellow inmates, followed by a move to an experimental open prison.